#: using-morefeatures.docbook:237
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The &knode; composer provides many features, especially for posting and "
"replying to articles."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: using-morefeatures.docbook:241
#, no-c-format
msgid "Publish Articles in Multiple Newsgroups"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: using-morefeatures.docbook:243
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By selecting the Button <guilabel>Browse</guilabel> you can choose additional "
"newsgroups you want to publish your article in."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: using-morefeatures.docbook:248
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is generally undesirable to post articles in multiple newsgroups: please "
"think twice about it; if you are not sure where to post your article ask in one "
"of the possible groups &mdash; somebody will tell you were to post."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: using-morefeatures.docbook:256
#, no-c-format
msgid "Redirect Followups"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: using-morefeatures.docbook:258
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The main use of this feature is when a thread has gone off topic for the "
"newsgroup in which it is posted; for example, a thread may start in a &kde; "
"newsgroup discussing how to redirect a followup in &knode;, but may leads to a "
"dicussion about graphical and text based newsreaders."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: using-morefeatures.docbook:264
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Sometimes it happens that usenet users post an article into the wrong "
"newsgroup; very often those articles are just ignored. If it looks like the "
"author did this unintentionally, you might like to tell them politely and make "
"the followup articles go into the right group."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: using-morefeatures.docbook:270
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Another reason for using <guilabel>Followup-To:</guilabel> "
"is a when dealing with articles cross-posted across in multiple newsgroups: you "
"should take care that the replies are only posted in one single newsgroup."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: using-morefeatures.docbook:274
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can activate this by filling the text box <guilabel>Followup-To:</guilabel>"
"; here you can enter the suitable group. If there are multiple newsgroups in "
"the <guilabel>Groups:</guilabel> field, they are shown in the drop-down list."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: using-morefeatures.docbook:281
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you enter <userinput>poster</userinput> here, instead of a newsgroup, the "
"replies will go directly to the author, not to the newsgroup."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: using-morefeatures.docbook:285
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Some people put an email address here, but this is not a valid entry: use "
"<userinput>poster</userinput> and correctly set your Reply-To address in the "
"normal &knode; settings."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: using-morefeatures.docbook:294
#, no-c-format
